author: Sean Shapiro
title: Rain not likely to wash away U.S. Grand Prix schedule
text:
Officials at Circuit of the Americas are preparing for wet weather when the United States Grand Prix comes to Austin this weekend.
Heavy rain is in the forecast for Friday and Saturday, and that could mean wet practice and qualifying sessions, and Sunday morning showers could affect the race.
